Free-surface elevations will be captured using high-speed imaging and tracked via particle image velocimetry (PIV). Wall impact pressures will be recorded using miniature piezoelectric sensors. The same quantities ($h(t)$, $p(t)$, $E_k(t)$, $\eta$) will be extracted from both experiments and simulations for direct quantitative comparison.

