\section{Granular Dampers: Mechanisms and Evidence}
\label{sec:granulardampers}

Granular dampers, also known as particle dampers, are passive vibration attenuation devices consisting of an enclosure partially filled with solid particles.
When the host structure oscillates, the particles move, collide, and interact with both the container walls and each other, dissipating kinetic energy through inelastic collisions and frictional losses.
Unlike traditional tuned mass or liquid dampers, granular dampers provide broadband energy dissipation, require no active control, and are effective over a wide range of excitation frequencies~\parencite[5716]{prasad2022damping}.

